You are right. The issue is that it requires to modify the TTML content, i.e. re-encoding it, while DASH-ing it.

Actually we mark the samples as 'redundant' when the repeat data that waere already sent. It seems that the players ignore it.

Please let me know what you think.

For the 'trun'/'tfhd' issue, I know understand. I'll investigate and let you know here.

For TTML, if the content is not prepared for DASHing, the constraint on the duration requires the DASHer to rewrite the TTML samples to modify the 'begin'/'end' values. In the principle the DASHer does not re-encode the content (e.g. it does not re-encode video when the RAP are not aligned). @cconcolato opinion on this?

@aleal-envivio Is my explanation clear about what we do with the 'redundant' flag?

It is usefull for extenal user of the library when using static linking. It allows to configure the module to load without having to modify the source. Here is some code that configure some modules:

```
